KNOWN BUGS or LIMITATIONS:

double scale = (double)(getHeight() - 2 * VERTICAL_BUFFER) / getNumTrials;

The bug is about the data type. When I first ran the program, the bars were 
occasionally not displayed onto the window. When I printed out the value of 
scale, the value showed zero. Then I noticed there was something wrong with 
data type. I used cast operator to solve this problem. 

Before assigning the value to scale variable, the cast operation converts 
integer type value to double type so that the result of the operation comes 
to double type.

The cast operation is in section 4.2.5 of the textbook.

