ANSWERS TO ASSIGNMENT README QUESTIONS (if applicable):

1. Probability of two heads: 0.25;
   Probability of one head and one tail: 0.5;
   Probability of two tails: 0.25.
   The first coin shows head, while the second coin show tail, the result will
show one head and one tail. In addition, the result will also show one head and 
one tail when the first shows tail and the second shows head. However, the result
will show two heads only if both of coins shows head, same as the result of two
tails. Therefore, the result of one head and one tail is different from the other.

2. 5000.

3. The largest value that worked correctly: 42949673.
   The value that overflowed: 42949674.


